<typeStatus id="800A488BEA260C33FBFAFF49F5D653A5" box="[1137,1188,152,178]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">type</typeStatus>
locality (
<figureCitation id="C78AEAACEA260C33FA98FF49F40853A5" box="[1299,1402,152,178]" captionStart="FIGURE 160" captionStartId="55.[151,254,1439,1463]" captionTargetBox="[226,1361,700,1412]" captionTargetId="figure-384@55.[226,1362,700,1412]" captionTargetPageId="55" captionText="FIGURE 160. Known localities in Mexico and Central America of Platyhydnobius andersoni (black square), P. bicolor (open triangle), P. calvario (open square), P. howdenorum (black triangle), P. latigra (black dots), P. newtonorum (asterisk)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5311002" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5311002/files/figure.png" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Fig. 160</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="6DC52A3BEA260C33FF4DFF6FF02153CF" bold="true" box="[198,339,190,216]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name refers to the 
<typeStatus id="800A488BEA260C33FDE2FF6FF3EE53CF" box="[617,668,190,216]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">type</typeStatus>
locality Cerro El Calvario.
